						               													<description>You play a long-retired knight of the once great but now disbanded knightly Order. Since becoming former knights, you and your remaining companions have been operating a modest bar together. One night, you have all been rudely awoken by threatening events and false accusations of mysterious origin. Split up and on the run, chased by agents of dangerous organizations and other threats to your peaceful retirement, you must hastily travel in secret across the realm and unravel the conspiracy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Neon Limbo: Redemption is a competitive game with some &amp;ldquo;common threat&amp;rdquo; elements. It is played over a fixed number of rounds, divided across three Chapters. Each round, you travel from location to location and choose from encounters of various degrees of difficulty to resolve. Encounters represent character choices and their resolution defines your character's personal path, traits, and story. By resolving encounters you can gather Support in the realm, but may also attract negative attention in the form of Glow tokens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to acquire the most Influence Points while avoiding accumulating too many Glow tokens which may cause you to lose in the end.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
